subtitle: We're all sent to this world on a mission.
Don't ever forget that.
Whether we ignore it, whether we embrace it, whether we're distracted.
We have a mission. And there will happen
not only once in our life, but at least once in our lifetime.
When you will be called upon to serve, you'll be called upon to do something
and something you're uncomfortable with doing.
And what do we do when we’re uncomfortable?
We try to avoid it.
Some of us procrastinate.
Some of us delay.
We all have our ways of escaping our calling.
But remember, it's your destiny and it's your gift.
It's not just responsibility.
It's a blessing.
It's a statement saying you need to accomplish something
with your life that no one else can accomplish but you.
And the very world itself
will make sure that you live up to your calling.
So Jonah goes onto the boat.
We all go out to our boats.
I'm going on vacation.
I'm going on a safari, on a siesta.
I'm going to find a way to numb my existential pain in life.
And we think we can escape our destiny.
You can never escape your destiny, whether you’re at sea or land,
physically or figuratively.
It will come back to haunt you. You can run
but you can't hide.
